around campaigns and causes they care about.

36:10.402 --> 36:11.870 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
I think we have already seen that post-election.

36:11.970 --> 36:15.140 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
We have seen lots of different groups thathave seen spikes in giving.

36:15.240 --> 36:18.910 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
ELIZABETH SUDA, Article 22: And each piece
helps clear some of the 80 million bombs that

36:19.010 --> 36:20.779 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
haven't yet exploded.

36:20.879 --> 36:28.086 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
I think our jewelry has this multilayered
impact, where the giver is consciously choosing

36:28.186 --> 36:32.257 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
something that has benefits for the people
that make it.

36:32.357 --> 36:35.660 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
We will still continue to use these hand tools.

36:35.760 --> 36:40.732 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
MIKE CERRE: We first discovered Elizabeth
Suda and her jewelry made from UXOs during

36:40.832 --> 36:45.870 align:left position:62.5%,start line:86.67% size:37.5%
President Obama's state visit to Laos in September,
when he pledged to nearly double the amount

36:45.970 --> 36:51.443 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
of money the U.S. spends each year cleaning
up UXOs, unexploded ordnance, dropped during

36:51.543 --> 36:53.311 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the Vietnam War.

36:53.411 --> 36:58.283 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
ELIZABETH SUDA: This is actually a cluster
bomb known as the pineapple, and it has aluminum

36:58.383 --> 37:01.052 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
fins here and then other aluminum components.

37:01.152 --> 37:06.424 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
They are also able to make plane parts hammered
down and put in the kiln, and you can actually

37:06.524 --> 37:10.962 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
get quite a few bracelets out of various pieces.

37:11.062 --> 37:16.634 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
The pieces really started as conversation
starters.

37:16.734 --> 37:24.576 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
The idea was to buy back the bombs and help
clear unexploded ordnance, and give people

37:24.676 --> 37:31.049 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
an entry point into a conversation about what
might otherwise be a forgotten part of history.

37:31.149 --> 37:36.588 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
MIKE CERRE: More than four decades since the
end of the Vietnam War, neighboring Laos is

37:36.688 --> 37:43.661 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
still littered with UXOs, unexploded ordnance,
which continue to kill and maim civilians,

37:43.761 --> 37:48.600 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
mostly children, and even some of these jewelry
makers, like this one, who lost an eye as

37:48.700 --> 37:50.635 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
a boy.

37:50.735 --> 37:55.907 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Proceeds from the sale of jewelry on Giving
Tuesday and throughout the year goes to MAG,

37:56.007 --> 38:01.212 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
the Mines Advisory Group, to safely clear
the artisans' fields of these still dangerous

38:01.312 --> 38:03.214 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
legacies of war.

38:03.314 --> 38:09.287 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
HENRY TIMMS: And the thing we have seen happen
over and over again is the most creative campaigns

38:09.387 --> 38:12.524 align:left position:62.5%,start line:86.67% size:37.5%
are coming from some of the smallest institutions,
right?

38:12.624 --> 38:15.226 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
what we often see is, those with the fewest
resources actually thinking of some really

38:15.326 --> 38:19.564 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
smart ideas to try and think about how to
approach Giving Tuesday in new ways.

38:19.664 --> 38:26.271 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
MIKE CERRE: Giving Tuesday and recycling bombs
into jewelry isn't as much about anti-consumerism

38:26.371 --> 38:31.409 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
as it is about buying, making and selling
stuff that benefits others and extends the

38:31.509 --> 38:35.647 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
gratification that comes from gift-giving
beyond the holidays.

38:35.747 --> 38:39.184 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
ELIZABETH SUDA: The Love Is a Bomb pieces,
I believe, are $185.

38:39.284 --> 38:43.721 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
People are shopping for holiday gifts that
they're going to give to somebody that they

38:43.821 --> 38:46.391 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
love or that they care about.

38:46.491 --> 38:51.663 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
And the jewelry that we offer is a symbol
of that love, both in terms of it being a

38:51.763 --> 38:54.832 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
gift, but in terms of the story that it carries.

38:54.933 --> 39:01.773 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
MIKE CERRE: Charlie Decker discovered the
story and Article 22's holiday booth in New

39:01.873 --> 39:07.178 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
York's Union Square and bought a matching
set of wedding rings made from bombs to give

39:07.278 --> 39:09.080 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
something back this holiday season.

39:09.180 --> 39:13.318 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
CHARLIE DECKER, Consumer: Hoping that, you
know, all the wounds get healed, and this

39:13.418 --> 39:16.588 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
is our little piece that we had to play in
it.

39:16.688 --> 39:26.564 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
MIKE CERRE: For the "PBS NewsHour," Mike Cerre,
reporting from New York.

39:26.664 --> 39:36.174 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now another installment of
our entrepreneur series.

39:36.274 --> 39:41.179 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Emily Feistritzer, who was a Catholic nun
in her youth, later became a teacher.

39:41.279 --> 39:46.684 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
In 2011, she created TEACH-NOW, a company
that trains and certifies teachers around

39:46.784 --> 39:47.719 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the world.

39:47.819 --> 39:50.588 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
It is now a multimillion-dollar business.

39:50.688 --> 39:54.726 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
William Brangham returns, having caught up
with Feistritzer in her Washington, D.C.,

39:54.826 --> 39:56.394 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
home.

39:56.494 --> 40:00.431 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: For Emily Feistritzer, lifeas an entrepreneur began early.

40:00.531 --> 40:05.069 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
As a young girl growing up in Kentucky, she
went door to door in her mostly Protestant

40:05.169 --> 40:06.871 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
neighborhood.

40:06.971 --> 40:09.707 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
EMILY FEISTRITZER, CEO, TEACH-NOW: Selling
statues of the Virgin Mary that glowed in

40:09.807 --> 40:10.708 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the dark.

40:10.808 --> 40:11.809 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

40:11.909 --> 40:13.077 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: That was your first business?

40:13.177 --> 40:15.346 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
EMILY FEISTRITZER: Yes, my first business.

40:15.446 --> 40:20.018 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: That business never took
off, but it led to her next stop, the Catholic

40:20.118 --> 40:21.853 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
convent.

40:21.953 --> 40:26.224 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
At 19, she became a nun, and got her first
job in education, teaching high school math

40:26.324 --> 40:28.092 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and science.

40:28.192 --> 40:35.199 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
EMILY FEISTRITZER: I would never, ever be
doing what I'm doing today if I hadn't learned

40:35.300 --> 40:40.705 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
the kind of focus and discipline that that
life provided.

40:40.805 --> 40:45.943 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
I mean, you were taught to be laser-focused.

40:46.044 --> 40:49.047 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: And you really do trace
it back to your time in the convent?

40:49.147 --> 40:51.182 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
EMILY FEISTRITZER: Absolutely.

40:51.282 --> 40:52.183 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Absolutely.

40:52.283 --> 40:55.787 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
There's no question about that.

40:55.887 --> 41:00.792 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
People sort of say, where did you get your
training to be a successful businesswoman?

41:00.892 --> 41:02.627 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And I say, the convent.

41:02.727 --> 41:06.497 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: She left the convent, and
the Catholic Church, at 31, earned a Ph.D

41:06.597 --> 41:10.668 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
and launched a career in education that hasspanned more than four decades.

41:10.768 --> 41:12.370 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
&nbsp;
She was a professor.

41:12.470 --> 41:16.541 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
She wrote books on teacher training, started
a clearinghouse on best practices.

41:16.641 --> 41:21.346 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
And then, a few years ago, she plopped down
half-a-million dollars of her own money to

41:21.446 --> 41:23.915 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
launch a brand-new digital company.

41:24.015 --> 41:27.452 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
You could very easily have just said, you
know what, it's time.

41:27.552 --> 41:31.956 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
I'm going to have a peaceful retirement andjust enjoy the end of your life.

41:32.056 --> 41:36.594 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Instead, you dove into what may be, arguably,
the most intense period of work in your life.

41:36.694 --> 41:38.129 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Why?

41:38.229 --> 41:41.632 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
EMILY FEISTRITZER: Well, I was sort of playing
around with retiring.

41:41.733 --> 41:49.273 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
I was already getting a Social Security check,and I really didn't like it.

41:49.374 --> 41:53.778 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
&nbsp;
I have to be engaged in something.

41:53.878 --> 41:56.314 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
And I didn't want to, like, do pottery.

41:56.414 --> 41:59.217 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: That decision has more than
paid off.

41:59.317 --> 42:05.556 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Today, her company, known as TEACH-NOW, has
15 full-time employees, and more than 40 part-time

42:05.656 --> 42:07.458 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
instructors around the world.

42:07.558 --> 42:14.432 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
EMILY FEISTRITZER: It's now bringing in revenues
of around $4 million and a profit margin of

42:14.532 --> 42:17.168 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
about 20 percent, 20-25 percent.

42:17.268 --> 42:23.708 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: TEACH-NOW charges $6,000
per person to take its nine-month teacher-certification

42:23.808 --> 42:25.510 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
program.

42:25.610 --> 42:28.579 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
That's a cheaper and faster alternative to
what most traditional universities offer.

42:28.679 --> 42:33.017 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
And since it began, more than 1,200 peoplehave completed the course.

42:33.117 --> 42:36.120 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Classrooms look like this.

42:36.220 --> 42:38.423 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Students log in virtually anywhere in the
world.

42:38.523 --> 42:40.825 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
And lessons are given by veteran teachers.

42:40.925 --> 42:44.095 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
Dan Roggenkamp lives and works in Taiwan.

42:44.195 --> 42:45.897 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
He's leading this discussion.

42:45.997 --> 42:50.234 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
DAN ROGGENKAMP, Teacher: So, we're looking
for as little redundancy in information as

42:50.334 --> 42:52.136 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
possible.

42:52.236 --> 42:58.476 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Before completion, however,
people like Walter Allen must spend at least

42:58.576 --> 43:02.847 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
12 weeks in a real classroom, where they are
filmed and monitored by mentors online.

43:02.947 --> 43:07.251 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
WALTER ALLEN, Teacher: As a teacher, it helps
a lot.

43:07.351 --> 43:13.057 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Like, I know a lot of first-year teachers
personally who didn't have to undergo any

43:13.157 --> 43:18.429 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
field experience prior to getting hired, and
sometimes that first year is like a disaster.

43:18.529 --> 43:22.433 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Allen is teaching reading
intervention at Kelley Miller Middle School

43:22.533 --> 43:24.035 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in Washington, D.C.

43:24.135 --> 43:27.638 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
It's a class designed to help students whohave fallen behind in English.

43:27.738 --> 43:32.443 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
He's aiming to not only be certified as a
special-ed instructor, but he also wants do

43:32.543 --> 43:34.378 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
something much bigger.

43:34.479 --> 43:41.152 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
WALTER ALLEN: Growing up, going to D.C. public
schools, elementary, middle school, high school,

43:41.252 --> 43:46.424 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
I didn't -- personally, I didn't have many
African-American teachers, African-American

43:46.524 --> 43:48.259 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
male teachers.

43:48.359 --> 43:52.163 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
So, enrolling into the TEACH-NOW program,
taking education seriously, graduating from

43:52.263 --> 43:59.804 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
college, furthering my education, all of this
allows me to become that idea, that possibility

43:59.904 --> 44:02.940 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
for African-American students that I teach
now.

44:03.040 --> 44:07.712 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
They see me inside of their classroom teaching
as an African-American male teacher and say,

44:07.812 --> 44:11.315 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
hey, maybe, one day, I can become a teacher.

44:11.415 --> 44:16.654 align:left position:62.5%,start line:86.67% size:37.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Kerri Valencia is an elementary
Spanish teacher in Washington, D.C.'s Sheridan

44:16.754 --> 44:18.523 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
School.

44:18.623 --> 44:21.792 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
She completed the TEACH-NOW certification
three years ago while living in Ecuador, where

44:21.893 --> 44:24.595 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
she was teaching English at an international
school.

44:24.695 --> 44:29.233 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Valencia had a bachelor's degree in Spanish,
but thought that wasn't going to be enough

44:29.333 --> 44:31.269 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
to land her a teaching job back in the U.S.

44:31.369 --> 44:35.172 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
KERRI VALENCIA, Teacher: And I was just really
drawn to the fact that it was a nine-month

44:35.273 --> 44:36.173 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
program.

44:36.274 --> 44:38.009 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I have a family.

44:38.109 --> 44:41.279 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
I wasn't in a place where I could go back
and do another four-year degree or two-year

44:41.379 --> 44:44.115 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
degree, which is kind of what looked my options
were.

44:44.215 --> 44:48.252 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Feistritzer says she's met
several teachers like Valencia, who came to

44:48.352 --> 44:51.489 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
the profession late or had been working, but
without certification.

44:51.589 --> 44:55.526 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
EMILY FEISTRITZER: So there's really been
a groundswell of interest in teaching on a

44:55.626 --> 45:02.066 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
part of mid-career switchers, people who've
raised a family and decided to do a career

45:02.166 --> 45:07.538 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
later in life, people who want to move in
and out of careers.

45:07.638 --> 45:10.308 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
So, that market, I saw coming.

45:10.408 --> 45:17.381 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
When you run the kind of program we're running,
which is not only so good, but it can be taken

45:17.481 --> 45:21.419 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
anywhere, any time, it's very desirable.

45:21.519 --> 45:26.057 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: As for what the future may
have in store, Feistritzer says she's keeping

45:26.157 --> 45:30.394 align:left position:62.5%,start line:86.67% size:37.5%
an open mind, even to another business opportunity
coming up.

45:30.494 --> 45:41.072 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm William Brangham
in Washington, D.C.

45:41.172 --> 45:48.813 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Finally tonight: the "NewsHour"
Bookshelf.

45:48.913 --> 45:54.685 align:left position:62.5%,start line:86.67% size:37.5%
Jeffrey Brown sits down with Pulitzer Prize-winning
author Michael Chabon about his new book,

45:54.785 --> 46:00.124 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
"Moonglow," and the blending of fact and fiction
in literary art.

46:00.224 --> 46:11.068 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JEFFREY BROWN: "Moonglow," a classic tune
performed by Benny Goodman, background music

46:11.168 --> 46:16.907 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
in the Berkeley, California, writing studio
of Michael Chabon, where he often works deep

46:17.008 --> 46:18.209 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
into the night.

46:18.309 --> 46:21.846 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
"Moonglow" is also the title of Chabon's new
book.

46:21.946 --> 46:26.817 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
A novel, it's presented as a kind of memoir,
blurring the lines between truth and fiction.

46:26.917 --> 46:29.654 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
MICHAEL CHABON, Author, "Moonglow": You're
telling a lie when you're writing a novel.

46:29.754 --> 46:30.655 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
A novel is a lie.

46:30.755 --> 46:31.656 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Yes.

46:31.756 --> 46:32.823 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Right.

46:32.923 --> 46:34.725 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
MICHAEL CHABON: It's the only good kind of
lie.

46:34.825 --> 46:37.495 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
It's the lie that you're telling to someone
with their permission, and not only with their

46:37.595 --> 46:38.829 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
permission, but at their invitation.

46:38.929 --> 46:43.501 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
So, the reader comes to the novel and says,
lie to me.

46:43.601 --> 46:44.502 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I want to hear it.

46:44.602 --> 46:45.503 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Like, tell me a story.

46:45.603 --> 46:46.704 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Yes.

46:46.804 --> 46:47.471 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
You, the author, say, let me tell you a good
lie.

46:47.571 --> 46:49.340 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MICHAEL CHABON: Exactly.

46:49.440 --> 46:53.711 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
And that's part of what is so beautiful about
that particular relationship, is that it's

46:53.811 --> 46:59.984 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
a kind of voluntary permission to deception,
just like with magic.

47:00.084 --> 47:06.791 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JEFFREY BROWN: In this case, the magic started
with an actual ad he found from a 1958 "Esquire"

47:06.891 --> 47:12.963 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
magazine for something called Chabon Scientific
Company that sold models of missiles that

47:13.064 --> 47:14.899 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
you can fly.

47:14.999 --> 47:19.370 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
MICHAEL CHABON: My name, C-H-A-B-O-N, if that's
your last name, you're related to me somehow.

47:19.470 --> 47:21.572 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
And there aren't very many Chabons in the
world.

47:21.672 --> 47:25.309 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JEFFREY BROWN: But this Chabon had never heard
of that company.

47:25.409 --> 47:26.410 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
No one had.

47:26.510 --> 47:29.213 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
So, he invented its story as part of "Moonglow."

47:29.313 --> 47:35.953 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
MICHAEL CHABON: I defy anyone using Google
to contradict anything I say about the history

47:36.053 --> 47:37.755 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
of Chabon Scientific Company in my book.

47:37.855 --> 47:38.856 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

47:38.956 --> 47:39.757 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
JEFFREY BROWN: Because there ain't no history.

47:39.857 --> 47:40.758 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MICHAEL CHABON: Not yet.

47:40.858 --> 47:41.759 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I mean, they may come forward.

47:41.859 --> 47:43.561 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: There is now.

47:43.661 --> 47:45.730 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
MICHAEL CHABON: The real -- the defendants
of the founding Chabon of that company may

47:45.830 --> 47:49.500 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
emerge to tell their version of the story.

47:49.600 --> 47:52.369 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
But, until that happens, Google can't help
you.

47:52.470 --> 47:54.271 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You're at my mercy.

47:54.371 --> 47:58.142 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JEFFREY BROWN: Then there was this man, Chabon's
real grandfather, who on his deathbed, under

47:58.242 --> 48:03.948 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
the influence of painkilling drugs, began
telling his then-26-year-old grandson unknown

48:04.048 --> 48:06.350 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
stories from his life.

48:06.450 --> 48:08.319 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
This too became fodder for the novel.

48:08.419 --> 48:12.757 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
MICHAEL CHABON: There is all this stuff I
was hearing that was clearly still there,

48:12.857 --> 48:16.660 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
you know, that was in his mind, in his memory,
in his experience, in his life, that I had

48:16.761 --> 48:17.661 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
never heard before.

48:17.762 --> 48:19.630 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
And it just was all kind of coming out.

48:19.730 --> 48:22.366 align:left position:62.5%,start line:93.33% size:37.5%
And I thought, like, you think you know somebody.

48:22.466 --> 48:23.701 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
You think you have heard their stories.

48:23.801 --> 48:25.603 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Right.

48:25.703 --> 48:30.641 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
MICHAEL CHABON: And then to suddenly, at the
very end, get this glimpse of an entire other

48:30.741 --> 48:35.513 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
life that I had never heard of before, not
that it was a life of dark secrets or anything

48:35.613 --> 48:38.682 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
like that, but just there was so much more,
so much more.

48:38.783 --> 48:43.988 align:left position:62.5%,start line:86.67% size:37.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: But then that opens the floodgates
for you, and you, being a novelist, get to

48:44.088 --> 48:45.222 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
play, right?

48:45.322 --> 48:47.825 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
MICHAEL CHABON: That's what I do with every
book.

48:47.925 --> 48:55.866 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
That procedure of taking bits and pieces of
an element of lived experience, of stories

48:55.966 --> 49:02.206 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
I have heard, anecdotes and research or whatever
it might be gets all swirled together with

49:02.306 --> 49:04.041 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the invention.

49:04.141 --> 49:08.145 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
The reader wants to hear the lie that sounds
true and ultimately, I think, in the case

49:08.245 --> 49:13.250 align:left position:62.5%,start line:86.67% size:37.5%
of fiction, in the case of a novel, that delivers
a truth -- a truth.

49:13.350 --> 49:19.256 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JEFFREY BROWN: To see Chabon's studio is to
peek into the brain that produces that invention,

49:19.356 --> 49:24.862 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
action figures, vintage science fiction and
fantasy novels, vinyl records, much of it

49:24.962 --> 49:29.500 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
connected to things he's written, from the
Pulitzer-Prize winning "Adventures of Kavalier

49:29.600 --> 49:35.406 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
&amp; Clay" to now the mash-up of "Moonglow,"
which explores war, family and technology

49:35.506 --> 49:40.344 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
in mid-century America and mixes historicalfigures with the fictional.

49:40.444 --> 49:45.749 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
War, rocketry, space travel, even -- you and
I have talked about this before when you're

49:45.850 --> 49:47.318 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
writing some of it, genre-bending.

49:47.418 --> 49:52.089 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
You know, it's a sort of memoir, but it getssort of into almost fantasy.

49:52.189 --> 49:53.958 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
MICHAEL CHABON: Love among people in their
golden years.

49:54.058 --> 49:54.959 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Yes.

49:55.059 --> 49:55.960 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Yes.

49:56.060 --> 49:56.961 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
A lot of things going on there.

49:57.061 --> 49:58.863 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
But that allows you the freedom.

49:58.963 --> 50:00.998 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
Once you have that freedom, you're off.

50:01.098 --> 50:01.999 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Right?

50:02.099 --> 50:03.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MICHAEL CHABON: Right.

50:03.100 --> 50:04.001 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And that's what it's all about.

50:04.101 --> 50:05.002 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
The facts are so dull.

50:05.102 --> 50:06.003 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

50:06.103 --> 50:07.771 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: So dull?

50:07.872 --> 50:13.210 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
MICHAEL CHABON: We turn to fiction, we turn
to a novel because fiction persuades us.

50:13.310 --> 50:19.783 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
All art persuades us that there is a pattern
to life, that there is meaning to life, that

50:19.884 --> 50:27.625 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
if you look at life the right way, you can
see sense in it, you can find meaning in it.

50:27.725 --> 50:29.093 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It might not be true.

50:29.193 --> 50:30.961 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Maybe that's an illusion.

50:31.061 --> 50:38.269 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Maybe that's like the greatest illusion of
the magic act of literature, but I don't care.

50:38.369 --> 50:39.470 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
That's what is good about it.

50:39.570 --> 50:40.871 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
That's what we turn to it for.

50:40.971 --> 50:43.474 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
JEFFREY BROWN: The new novel is "Moonglow."

50:43.574 --> 50:45.175 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
Michael Chabon, thank you for letting us visit.

50:45.276 --> 50:46.176 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
MICHAEL CHABON: Oh, absolutely.

50:46.277 --> 50:47.177 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Thank you, Jeff.

50:47.278 --> 50:51.015 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Thank you.

